    &lt;Title&gt;Excellent service as outpatient.&lt;/Title&gt;
    &lt;ScreenName&gt;Jim Cordiner&lt;/ScreenName&gt;
    &lt;CommentText&gt;Visited Chorley Hospital today for blood tests.  During visit enquired if x-ray, requested by GP only yesterday, could be arranged to avoid second visit.  X-ray Department checked that request had been received and organized that I could be x-rayed after blood tests.  I had about a 45 minute wait to have my bloods taken and by the time I returned to the X-ray Department there was only about a further 20 minutes to have the x-rays taken.  Altogether the visit was about 2 hours to get bloods and x-rays.  Staff were all very professional and helpful.  I was saved the time and expense of having to return to the hospital for a second visit by the efficiency of the staff.&lt;/CommentText&gt;
